  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Chop your<strong> potatoes</strong> (skins on) into small bite-sized pieces and add<strong> </strong>to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Sprinkle your <strong>dried oregano</strong> all over, give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1690285221322-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
